52:39.880 --> 52:41.800
He's... Hmm? He's clueing for looks.

52:53.040 --> 52:54.880
Mr.. Holmes?

52:59.920 --> 53:02.519
Mr.. Holmes! I'm calling
the police. Oh, no...

53:02.520 --> 53:04.239
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

53:04.240 --> 53:06.479
No, look, this is
a famous detective,

53:06.480 --> 53:09.279
it's Sherlock Holmes and
his partner, John Hamish Watson.

53:09.280 --> 53:10.679
What do you think you're doing?

53:10.680 --> 53:15.400
Don't compromise the
integrity of the...

53:20.640 --> 53:21.880
Crime scene.

53:28.080 --> 53:29.720
Yeah, that.

53:49.720 --> 53:51.000
Wakey-wakey!

53:51.440 --> 53:52.719
Oh, my God.

53:52.720 --> 53:54.599
Greg... Is that Greg?

53:54.600 --> 53:56.999
Get up. I'm going to
put you two in a taxi.

53:57.000 --> 53:59.679
I managed to square things
with the desk sergeant.

53:59.680 --> 54:02.199
Ha! What a couple of lightweights -

54:02.200 --> 54:04.239
you couldn't even make it
to closing time!

54:04.240 --> 54:05.760
- Can you whisper?
- Not really!

54:09.640 --> 54:11.480
Come on.

54:23.200 --> 54:26.559
Well, thanks for a...

54:26.560 --> 54:28.919
You know... an evening.

54:28.920 --> 54:29.920
It was awful.

54:29.921 --> 54:32.999
Yeah. I was going to pretend, but...

54:33.000 --> 54:34.639
it was, truly.

54:34.640 --> 54:37.279
That woman, Tessa... What?

54:37.280 --> 54:39.759
Dated a ghost, most interesting
case for months.

54:39.760 --> 54:41.320
