He had a mask on.

59:31.200 --> 59:33.279
He's stealing
the identity of corpses,

59:33.280 --> 59:36.559
getting their names
from the obituary columns.

59:36.560 --> 59:37.879
All single men.

59:37.880 --> 59:39.319
He's using the dead man's flat

59:39.320 --> 59:41.959
under the assumption
it will be empty for a while.

59:41.960 --> 59:43.319
Free love nest.

59:43.320 --> 59:44.320
I feel sick.

59:44.320 --> 59:45.320
It's gruesome.

59:45.321 --> 59:48.080
That's awful. Clever... Bastard!

59:52.320 --> 59:54.599
Hello, Tessa.

59:54.600 --> 59:56.079
Meanwhile, back to business.

59:56.080 --> 59:57.840
No-one wants to use
a dead man's home.

59:59.240 --> 01:00:01.279
At least not until
it's been cleared.

01:00:01.280 --> 01:00:04.439
So, he disguises hiMs..elf.

01:00:04.440 --> 01:00:07.359
Steals the man's home,
steals his identity.

01:00:07.360 --> 01:00:09.999
But only for one night.
Then he's gone.

01:00:10.000 --> 01:00:12.159
He's not a ghost, John.
He's a Mayfly.

01:00:12.160 --> 01:00:13.520
He lives for a day.

01:00:14.720 --> 01:00:18.639
So, what was it
he was looking for?

01:00:18.640 --> 01:00:19.679
Job?

01:00:19.680 --> 01:00:21.159
Gardener. Cook.

01:00:21.160 --> 01:00:22.759
Private nurse. I do security work.

01:00:22.760 --> 01:00:23.960
Maid.

01:00:25.240 --> 01:00:27.120
Obvious. You all work
for the same person.

01:00:41.600 --> 01:00:44.039
No, no, not the same employer. Damn!

01:00:44.040 --> 01:00:45.439
Come on, we can do this.

01:00:45.440 --> 01:00:46.559
Ideal night out?

01:00:46.560 --> 01:00:47.879
Clay-pigeon shooting.

01:00:47.880 --> 01:00:48.999
Line dancing.

01:00:49.000 --> 01:00:50.079
Pictures.

01:00:50.080 --> 01:00:51.879
Wine in front of the telly.

01:00:51.880 --> 01:00:53.600
Dungeon.

01:00:54.680 --> 01:00:56.519
Make-up? Clarins.

01:00:56.520 --> 01:00:57.919
No7.

01:00:57.920 --> 01:00:59.959
Maybelline. Nothing special.

01:00:59.960 --> 01:01:00.920
Whatever's cheap.

01:01:00.921 --> 01:01:02.599
Perfume?

01:01:02.600 --> 01:01:04.679
Chanel. Chanel. Chanel.

01:01:04.680 --> 01:01:07.120
Chanel. Estee Lauder.

01:01:08.320 --> 01:01:09.759
Ideal man?

01:01:09.760 --> 01:01:11.039
George Clooney.

01:01:11.040 --> 01:01:12.559
Oh...! Home-loving.

01:01:12.560 --> 01:01:14.519
He'd have to like cuddling.

01:01:14.520 --> 01:01:17.079
Caring. Ten things.

01:01:17.080 --> 01:01:19.279
One - someone who isn't
competitive with other men.

01:01:19.280 --> 01:01:21.399
Two - someone who isn't constantly

01:01:21.400 --> 01:01:24.879
trying to define hiMs..elf
by his masculinity...

01:01:24.880 --> 01:01:28.719
There's a unifying
factor, there has to be.

01:01:28.720 --> 01:01:30.600
None of you reported
anything stolen.

01:01:32.880 --> 01:01:36.679
Security guard, gardener, cook,
maid, private nurse.

01:01:36.680 --> 01:01:38.559
He's romancing his way
up a pecking order.

01:01:38.560 --> 01:01:41.520
Somebody's pecking order.
Come on, think. Unless...

01:01:42.640 --> 01:01:44.639
Do you have a secret
you've never told anyone?

01:01:44.640 --> 01:01:46.159
No.

01:01:46.160 --> 01:01:48.039
Gotcha! What do you mean?

01:01:48.040 --> 01:01:50.519
Everyone has secrets and
they all replied too quickly.

01:01:50.520 --> 01:01:53.319
Got to go. See you. No... Wait!
Bye-bye. Wait!

01:01:53.320 --> 01:01:56.039
Sorry, sexy, some secrets
have to stay secret.

01:01:56.040 --> 01:01:57.840
Enjoy the wedding.

01:02:00.240 --> 01:02:03.679
Why? WHY would he date all of those
women and not return their calls?

01:02:03.680 --> 01:02:06.199
You're missing
the obvious, mate. Am I?

01:02:06.200 --> 01:02:07.639
He's a man.

01:02:07.640 --> 01:02:09.719
But why would he
change his identity?

01:02:09.720 --> 01:02:11.120
Maybe he's married.

01:02:13.080 --> 01:02:16.039
Oh... Married.

01:02:16.040 --> 01:02:17.159
Obvious, really.

01:02:17.160 --> 01:02:18.879
Our Mayfly Man
was trying to escape

01:02:18.880 --> 01:02:20.599
the suffocating
chains of domesticity

01:02:20.600 --> 01:02:22.839
and instead of endless nights in
watching the telly

01:02:22.840 --> 01:02:26.519
or going to barbecues with the awful,
dreadful, boring people he couldn't stand,

01:02:26.520 --> 01:02:29.920
he used his wits, cleverness and powers
of disguise to play the field. He was...

01:02:32.640 --> 01:02:34.279
On second thoughts,

01:02:34.280 --> 01:02:37.279
I probably should have told you
about the elephant in the room.

01:02:37.280 --> 01:02:39.919
However, it does help
to further illustrate

01:02:39.920 --> 01:02:41.799
how invaluable John is to me.

01:02:41.800 --> 01:02:45.479
I can read a crime scene the way
he can understand a human being.

01:02:45.480 --> 01:02:48.439
I used to think that's what made me
special - quite frankly I still do.

01:02:48.440 --> 01:02:49.639
But a word to the wise,

01:02:49.640 --> 01:02:52.479
should any of you require
the services of either of us,

01:02:52.480 --> 01:02:54.319
I will solve your murder,

01:02:54.320 --> 01:02:57.199
but it takes John Watson
to save your life.

01:02:57.200 --> 01:02:58.799
Trust me on that, I should know,

01:02:58.800 --> 01:03:01.040
he's saved mine so many times
and in so many ways.

01:03:03.480 --> 01:03:07.119
This blog is the story of two men

01:03:07.120 --> 01:03:10.599
and their, frankly,
ridiculous adventures

01:03:10.600 --> 01:03:13.480
of murder, mystery and mayhem.

01:03:15.320 --> 01:03:18.280
But from now on,
there's a new story.

01:03:19.760 --> 01:03:21.680
A bigger adventure.

01:03:23.280 --> 01:03:24.599
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:03:24.600 --> 01:03:29.199
pray, charge your glasses
and be upstanding.

01:03:29.200 --> 01:03:31.239
Today begin the adventures

01:03:31.240 --> 01:03:33.119
of Mary Elizabeth Watson

01:03:33.120 --> 01:03:34.959
and John Hamish Watson.

01:03:34.960 --> 01:03:39.080
The two reasons why
every single one of us is...

01:03:56.800 --> 01:03:57.959
What did you say?

01:03:57.960 --> 01:04:04.639
You said... "John
Hamish Watson."

01:04:04.640 --> 01:04:07.080
You said that. You said "Hamish."

01:04:08.480 --> 01:04:10.599
This is a famous detective,
it's Sherlock Holmes

01:04:10.600 --> 01:04:12.399
and his partner, John Hamish Watson.

01:04:12.400 --> 01:04:14.319
How did you know?

01:04:14.320 --> 01:04:16.519
How did YOU know his middle name?

01:04:16.520 --> 01:04:18.640
He never tells anyone, he hates it.

01:04:22.600 --> 01:04:24.519
John "H" Watson?

01:04:24.520 --> 01:04:25.960
Yep.

01:04:33.000 --> 01:04:35.279
Henry? Shut up.

01:04:35.280 --> 01:04:36.519
Humphrey?

01:04:36.520 --> 01:04:38.239
Shut up.

01:04:38.240 --> 01:04:39.240
Higgins?

01:04:41.080 --> 01:04:43.159
'Go away!'

01:04:43.160 --> 01:04:45.839
It took him years to confide in me.

01:04:45.840 --> 01:04:49.959
Oh... That's my
birth certificate.

01:04:49.960 --> 01:04:51.200
Yep.

01:04:55.600 --> 01:04:57.840
And the woman - she knew.

01:05:00.040 --> 01:05:01.760
Hamish.

01:05:03.120 --> 01:05:04.799
John Hamish Watson,

01:05:04.800 --> 01:05:07.839
just if you were
looking for baby names.

01:05:07.840 --> 01:05:09.680
God knows where she is.

01:05:14.480 --> 01:05:16.400
Out of my head, I am busy!

01:05:17.920 --> 01:05:20.279
There's only one time
that name's been made public.

01:05:20.280 --> 01:05:22.199
Does it have to be on the invitation?

01:05:22.200 --> 01:05:24.199
It's your name.

01:05:24.200 --> 01:05:25.960
It's traditional... It's funny...

01:05:29.040 --> 01:05:30.520
'Enjoy the wedding...'

01:05:35.200 --> 01:05:36.639
Enjoy the wedding.

01:05:36.640 --> 01:05:38.759
The wedding.
You knew about the wedding.

01:05:38.760 --> 01:05:41.279
More importantly, you'd seen
a wedding invitation.

01:05:41.280 --> 01:05:43.519
Now barely 100 people
had seen that invitation.

01:05:43.520 --> 01:05:45.639
The Mayfly Man only saw five women.

01:05:45.640 --> 01:05:47.799
For one person
to be in both groups...

01:05:47.800 --> 01:05:49.399
could be a coincidence.

01:05:49.400 --> 01:05:51.519
Oh, Sherlock!

01:05:51.520 --> 01:05:53.719
What do we say about coincidences?

01:05:53.720 --> 01:05:55.159
The universe is rarely so lazy.

01:05:55.160 --> 01:05:58.199
So, the balance of probability is?
Someone went to great lengths

01:05:58.200 --> 01:06:00.522
to find out something about this wedding.
What great

01:06:00.534 --> 01:06:02.559
lengths? They lied.
Assumed false identities.

01:06:02.560 --> 01:06:04.519
Which suggests? Criminal intent.

01:06:04.520 --> 01:06:05.759
Also suggests?

01:06:05.760 --> 01:06:07.159
Intelligence, planning.

01:06:07.160 --> 01:06:09.600
Clearly. But more importantly?

01:06:11.120 --> 01:06:12.480
The Mayfly Man.

01:06:13.640 --> 01:06:17.079
The Mayfly Man is... Here today!

01:06:17.080 --> 01:06:19.880
Ooh, sorry. I...

01:06:21.360 --> 01:06:22.519
Another glass, sir?

01:06:22.520 --> 01:06:24.319
Thank you, yes, thank you. Yes.

01:06:24.320 --> 01:06:26.600
Something's going to happen,
right here.

01:06:29.920 --> 01:06:31.039
Now, where were we?

01:06:31.040 --> 01:06:32.040
Could be any second.

01:06:35.800 --> 01:06:37.159
You have control of the room.

01:06:37.160 --> 01:06:38.719
Ah, yes.

01:06:38.720 --> 01:06:41.839
Raising glasses and standing up.
Very good. Thank you.

01:06:41.840 --> 01:06:43.279
Don't lose it.

01:06:43.280 --> 01:06:45.560
And down again.

01:06:53.520 --> 01:06:54.679
Ladies and gentlemen,

01:06:54.680 --> 01:06:56.999
people tell you not
to milk a good speech.

01:06:57.000 --> 01:06:59.400
Get off early, leave 'em laughing.

01:07:00.920 --> 01:07:03.639
Wise advice I'll certainly
try to bear in mind.

01:07:03.640 --> 01:07:06.519
But for now... part two!

01:07:06.520 --> 01:07:09.039
Part two is more action-based.

01:07:09.040 --> 01:07:12.759
I'm going to walk around,
shake things up a bit.

01:07:12.760 --> 01:07:15.559
Who'd go to a wedding?
That's the question.

01:07:15.560 --> 01:07:18.199
Who would bother
to go to any lengths

01:07:18.200 --> 01:07:20.240
to get theMs..elves to a wedding?

01:07:21.840 --> 01:07:23.119
Well, everyone.

01:07:23.120 --> 01:07:25.679
Weddings are great, love a wedding.
What's he doing?

01:07:25.680 --> 01:07:27.439
Something's wrong.

01:07:27.440 --> 01:07:28.959
And John's great too.

01:07:28.960 --> 01:07:31.599
Haven't said that enough,
barely scratched the surface.

01:07:31.600 --> 01:07:32.959
I could go on all night

01:07:32.960 --> 01:07:37.279
about the depth and complexity
of his jumpers,

01:07:37.280 --> 01:07:39.599
and he can cook.

01:07:39.600 --> 01:07:43.160
Does... erm... a thing.
A thing with peas...

01:07:44.400 --> 01:07:46.639
Once. Might not be peas,
might not be him.

01:07:46.640 --> 01:07:49.639
But he's got a great singing voice,
or somebody does.

01:07:49.640 --> 01:07:51.920
Too many, too many,
too many, too many!

01:07:53.280 --> 01:07:56.039
Sorry, too many jokes about John.

01:07:56.040 --> 01:07:59.039
Now... Criminal intent.

01:07:59.040 --> 01:08:00.719
Where was I? Ah, yes.

01:08:00.720 --> 01:08:02.559
Extraordinary lengths.

01:08:02.560 --> 01:08:04.279
Speech. Speech.

01:08:04.280 --> 01:08:05.999
Let's talk about...

01:08:06.000 --> 01:08:08.480
All of which is suggestive of...

01:08:09.720 --> 01:08:12.559
Murder! Sorry, did I say murder?

01:08:12.560 --> 01:08:13.839
I meant to say marriage.

01:08:13.840 --> 01:08:16.439
But, you know,
they're quite similar procedures,

01:08:16.439 --> 01:08:17.679
when you think about it.

01:08:17.680 --> 01:08:19.519
The participants tend
to know each other

01:08:19.520 --> 01:08:21.279
and it's over
when one of them's dead.

01:08:21.279 --> 01:08:24.759
In fairness, murder is a lot quicker
though. Janine, what about this one?

01:08:24.760 --> 01:08:26.495
Acceptably hot? More
importantly, his

01:08:26.506 --> 01:08:28.759
girlfriend's wearing new
uncomfortable underwear

01:08:28.760 --> 01:08:30.745
and hasn't bothered to
pick this thread off his

01:08:30.756 --> 01:08:32.919
jacket, or point out the
grease smudge on his neck.

01:08:32.920 --> 01:08:35.559
He's going home alone.
Also he's a comics and sci-fi geek,

01:08:35.560 --> 01:08:38.519
they're always tremendously
grateful, really put the hours in.

01:08:38.520 --> 01:08:40.158
Jeff, the gents.

01:08:40.160 --> 01:08:41.439
Loos now, please.

01:08:41.439 --> 01:08:44.399
Greg. The loos, please. Why?

01:08:44.399 --> 01:08:46.640
Oh, I don't know,
maybe it's your TURN.

01:08:47.720 --> 01:08:49.639
Yeah, actually,
now you mention it.

01:08:49.640 --> 01:08:52.439
Sherlock, any chance of a...
An end date for this speech?

01:08:52.439 --> 01:08:53.519
Got to cut the cake.

01:08:53.520 --> 01:08:55.559
Oh, ladies and gentlemen,

01:08:55.560 --> 01:08:58.319
can't stand it when I finally
get the chance to speak for once.

01:08:58.319 --> 01:08:59.639
Vatican cameos.

01:08:59.640 --> 01:09:01.559
What did he say?
What does that mean?

01:09:01.560 --> 01:09:03.519
Battle stations,
someone's going to die.

01:09:03.520 --> 01:09:04.800
What?!

01:09:05.880 --> 01:09:08.560
Narrow it down. Narrow it down.

01:09:09.840 --> 01:09:11.639
Narrow it down!

01:09:11.640 --> 01:09:13.399
Argh! No, no!

01:09:13.399 --> 01:09:15.840
Not you!

01:09:17.240 --> 01:09:20.439
You. It's always you.

01:09:20.439 --> 01:09:23.200
John Watson, you keep me right.

01:09:24.840 --> 01:09:26.118
What do I do?

01:09:26.120 --> 01:09:27.759
You've already done it.

01:09:27.760 --> 01:09:29.879
Don't solve the murder.

01:09:29.880 --> 01:09:31.078
Save the life.

01:09:31.080 --> 01:09:33.559
Sorry, off piste a bit.

01:09:33.560 --> 01:09:34.879
Back now. Phew!

01:09:34.880 --> 01:09:37.800
Let's play a game.
Let's play murder.

01:09:39.200 --> 01:09:40.319
Sherlock!

01:09:40.319 --> 01:09:43.198
Imagine someone's going to
get murdered at a wedding.

01:09:43.200 --> 01:09:44.559
Who exactly would you pick?

01:09:44.560 --> 01:09:47.559
I think you're a popular choice
at the moment, dear.

01:09:47.560 --> 01:09:50.559
If someone could move Mr..s Hudson's
glass just slightly out of reach,

01:09:50.560 --> 01:09:51.560
that would be lovely.

01:09:51.560 --> 01:09:55.840
More importantly, who could you
only kill at a wedding?

01:09:57.200 --> 01:09:58.919
Most people you can kill
any old place.

01:09:58.920 --> 01:09:59.999
As a mental exercise,

01:10:00.000 --> 01:10:02.399
I've often planned the murder
of friends and colleagues.

01:10:02.400 --> 01:10:03.519
Now, John, I'd poison.

01:10:03.520 --> 01:10:06.599
Sloppy eater, dead easy. I've given
him chemicals and compounds,

01:10:06.600 --> 01:10:08.079
that way he's never even noticed.

01:10:08.080 --> 01:10:10.319
He missed a whole Wednesday once,
didn't have a clue.

01:10:10.320 --> 01:10:13.879
Lestrade's so easy to kill it's a miracle
no-one's succumbed to the temptation.

01:10:13.880 --> 01:10:15.745
I've got keys to my
brother's house, I could

01:10:15.757 --> 01:10:17.759
break in and asphyxiate
him, if the whim arose.

01:10:17.760 --> 01:10:19.559
He's pissed, isn't he? Ow!

01:10:19.560 --> 01:10:21.119
So, once again,

01:10:21.120 --> 01:10:23.679
who could you only kill here?

01:10:23.680 --> 01:10:25.239
Clearly it's a rare opportunity,

01:10:25.240 --> 01:10:27.199
so it's someone
who doesn't get out much.

01:10:27.200 --> 01:10:29.119
Someone for whom
a planned social encounter

01:10:29.120 --> 01:10:31.359
known about months in advance
is an exception.

01:10:31.360 --> 01:10:33.000
Has to be a unique opportunity.

01:10:34.400 --> 01:10:36.679
And since killing someone
in public is difficult,

01:10:36.680 --> 01:10:38.839
killing them in private
isn't an option.

01:10:38.840 --> 01:10:42.239
Someone who lives in an inaccessible
or unknown location, then.

01:10:42.240 --> 01:10:43.959
Someone private perhaps,

01:10:43.960 --> 01:10:46.000
obsessed with personal security.

01:10:47.440 --> 01:10:49.320
Possibly someone under threat.

01:10:53.960 --> 01:10:56.479
Major James Sholto, who he?
I don't think he's coming.

01:10:56.480 --> 01:10:57.480
He'll be there.

01:10:57.481 --> 01:10:59.359
Where are you living these days?

01:10:59.360 --> 01:11:01.439
Oh, way out in
the middle of nowhere.

01:11:01.440 --> 01:11:03.039
The press and families
gave him hell.

01:11:03.040 --> 01:11:04.880
He gets more death threats than you.

01:11:06.280 --> 01:11:08.319
A recluse?

01:11:08.320 --> 01:11:10.359
Small household staff.

01:11:10.360 --> 01:11:12.439
Job? Gardener. Cook.
Private nurse. Maid.

01:11:12.440 --> 01:11:14.439
High turnover
for additional security.

01:11:14.440 --> 01:11:17.479
I do security work. Probably all
signed confidentiality agreements.

01:11:17.480 --> 01:11:19.298
Do you have a secret
you've never told anyone?

01:11:19.310 --> 01:11:19.920
No.

01:11:19.921 --> 01:11:22.519
There is another question that
remains. Rather a big one,

01:11:22.520 --> 01:11:25.199
a huge one - how would you do it?
How do you kill someone in public?

01:11:25.200 --> 01:11:26.999
There has to be a way.
This has been planned.

01:11:27.000 --> 01:11:29.039
Mr.. Holmes! Hello, Archie,
what's your theory?

01:11:29.040 --> 01:11:31.479
Get this right and there's
a headless nun in it for you.

01:11:31.480 --> 01:11:34.199
The invisible man could do it.
The who, what, why, when, where?

01:11:34.200 --> 01:11:38.640
The invisible man with the invisible knife.
The one who tried to kill the Guardsman.

01:11:54.680 --> 01:11:55.839
Bainbridge?

01:11:55.840 --> 01:11:57.560
Bainbridge!

01:12:05.080 --> 01:12:08.599
(Oh, not just planned -
planned and rehearsed.)

01:12:08.600 --> 01:12:12.359
Ladies and gentlemen,
there will now be a short interlude.

01:12:12.360 --> 01:12:14.440
The bride and groom...

01:12:17.160 --> 01:12:19.119
The bride and groom.

01:12:19.120 --> 01:12:20.947
Major Sholto's going to
be murdered, I don't

01:12:20.959 --> 01:12:22.879
know how or by whom, but
it's going to happen.

01:12:22.880 --> 01:12:25.439
Excuse me, coming through.
Consulting.

01:12:25.440 --> 01:12:29.959
Stay here. Please be careful.
Excuse me. Coming through.

01:12:29.960 --> 01:12:32.439
Excuse me.

01:12:32.440 --> 01:12:34.639
I'm sorry, one more.
Oops. I'm so sorry.

01:12:34.640 --> 01:12:35.640
Thank you.

01:13:01.120 --> 01:13:04.159
How can you not remember which room?
You remember everything.

01:13:04.160 --> 01:13:06.560
I have to delete something! 207.

01:13:13.600 --> 01:13:16.520
Major Sholto? Major Sholto!

01:13:18.320 --> 01:13:21.919
Major Sholto! If someone's about
to make an attempt on my life,

01:13:21.920 --> 01:13:24.359
it won't be the first time.
I'm ready.

01:13:24.360 --> 01:13:26.359
Major, let us in.
Kick the door down.

01:13:26.360 --> 01:13:27.559
I really wouldn't.

01:13:27.560 --> 01:13:32.119
I have a gun in my hand and
a lifetime of unfortunate reflexes.

01:13:32.120 --> 01:13:33.730
You're not safe in there.
Whoever's after

01:13:33.742 --> 01:13:35.479
you, we know a locked
room doesn't stop him.

01:13:35.480 --> 01:13:37.439
The invisible man
with the invisible knife.

01:13:37.440 --> 01:13:39.428
I don't know how he does it.
I can't stop him and

01:13:39.440 --> 01:13:41.279
that means he'll do it again!
Solve it, then!

01:13:41.280 --> 01:13:43.119
I'm sorry?

01:13:43.120 --> 01:13:46.239
You're the famous Mr.. Holmes,
solve the case, on you go.

01:13:46.240 --> 01:13:48.879
Tell me how he did it
and I'll open the door.

01:13:48.880 --> 01:13:51.159
Please, this is no time for games,

01:13:51.160 --> 01:13:52.639
just let us in, you're in danger!

01:13:52.640 --> 01:13:54.199
So are you,
so long as you're here.

01:13:54.200 --> 01:13:57.119
Please, leave me.

01:13:57.120 --> 01:14:00.639
Despite my reputation, I really
don't approve of collateral damage.

01:14:00.640 --> 01:14:03.839
Solve it. Sorry? Solve it and
he'll open the door, like he said.

01:14:03.840 --> 01:14:07.079
I couldn't solve it before, how can I
solve it now? Because it matters now.

01:14:07.080 --> 01:14:10.119
What are you talking about? Get your
wife under control! She's right.

01:14:10.120 --> 01:14:11.999
Oh, you've changed!
No, she is. Shut up!

01:14:12.000 --> 01:14:14.279
You are not a puzzle-solver,
you never have been.

01:14:14.280 --> 01:14:15.399
You're a drama queen!

01:14:15.400 --> 01:14:19.160
Now, there's a man in there about
to die, the game is on - solve it!

01:14:34.920 --> 01:14:36.000
Bainbridge?

01:14:38.720 --> 01:14:40.200
Bainbridge!

01:14:43.320 --> 01:14:45.679
Though in fairness,
he's a drama queen too. I know.

01:14:45.680 --> 01:14:47.759
Major Sholto, no-one's
coming to kill you.

01:14:47.760 --> 01:14:50.559
I'm afraid you've already
been killed several hours ago.

01:14:50.560 --> 01:14:51.719
What did you say?

01:14:51.720 --> 01:14:53.279
Don't take off your belt.

01:14:53.280 --> 01:14:54.799
My belt?

01:14:54.800 --> 01:14:55.919
His belt, yes.

01:14:55.920 --> 01:14:58.319
Bainbridge was stabbed
hours before we even saw him,

01:14:58.320 --> 01:14:59.879
but it was through his belt.

01:14:59.880 --> 01:15:01.719
Tight belt, worn high on the waist.

01:15:01.720 --> 01:15:03.719
Very easy to push a small blade
through the fabric

01:15:03.720 --> 01:15:04.959
and you wouldn't even feel it.

01:15:04.960 --> 01:15:07.839
The belt would bind the flesh
together when it was tied tight.

01:15:07.840 --> 01:15:10.439
Exactly. But when you took it off...
Delayed-action stabbing.

01:15:10.440 --> 01:15:13.319
All the time in the world
to create an alibi. Major Sholto?

01:15:13.320 --> 01:15:14.600
So...

01:15:17.400 --> 01:15:20.679
I was to be killed by my uniform.

01:15:20.680 --> 01:15:23.000
How appropriate.

01:15:25.080 --> 01:15:26.559
He solved the case, Major,

01:15:26.560 --> 01:15:29.559
you're supposed to open
the door now. A deal is a deal.

01:15:29.560 --> 01:15:31.599
I'm not even supposed to
have this any more,

01:15:31.600 --> 01:15:33.719
they gave me special
dispensation to keep it.

01:15:33.720 --> 01:15:36.039
I couldn't imagine life
out of this uniform.

