but not at John's wedding!

01:16:12.320 --> 01:16:16.359
We wouldn't do that,
would we, you and me?

01:16:16.360 --> 01:16:19.120
We would never do that
to John Watson.

01:16:24.240 --> 01:16:25.599
I'm going to break it down.

01:16:25.600 --> 01:16:27.640
Wait, wait, wait, you won't have to.

01:16:33.920 --> 01:16:36.559
I believe I am in need
of medical attention.

01:16:36.560 --> 01:16:39.360
I believe I'm your doctor.

01:16:54.960 --> 01:16:57.199
Pretty good.

01:16:57.200 --> 01:16:59.279
Just hold your nerve
on your turning.

01:16:59.280 --> 01:17:00.959
Why do we have to rehearse?

01:17:00.960 --> 01:17:03.199
Because we are about to
dance together in public

01:17:03.200 --> 01:17:04.720
and your skills are appalling.

01:17:06.320 --> 01:17:08.319
Wow, you're a good teacher. Hmm.

01:17:08.320 --> 01:17:10.159
And you're a brilliant dancer.

01:17:10.160 --> 01:17:12.039
Can I let you in
on something, Janine?

01:17:12.040 --> 01:17:13.519
Go on, then.

01:17:13.520 --> 01:17:15.599
I love dancing,
I've always loved it.

01:17:15.600 --> 01:17:16.679
Seriously?

01:17:16.680 --> 01:17:17.680
Watch out.

01:17:21.680 --> 01:17:24.199
Oh!

01:17:24.200 --> 01:17:26.559
Never really comes up
in crime work, but, you know,

01:17:26.560 --> 01:17:29.439
I live in hope of the right case.
Oh, I wish you weren't...

01:17:29.440 --> 01:17:32.599
whatever it is you are.

01:17:32.600 --> 01:17:35.439
I know. Well, glad to see
you've pulled, Sherlock,

01:17:35.440 --> 01:17:38.279
what with murderers
running riot at my wedding.

01:17:38.280 --> 01:17:39.959
One murderer... One nearly murderer.

01:17:39.960 --> 01:17:42.359
Loves to exaggerate -
you should try living with him.

01:17:42.360 --> 01:17:43.879
Sherlock.

01:17:43.880 --> 01:17:45.639
Got him for you.

01:17:45.640 --> 01:17:48.759
Ah, the photographer,
excellent. Thank you.

01:17:48.760 --> 01:17:51.119
May I have a look at your camera?

01:17:51.120 --> 01:17:54.119
Erm, what's this about?
I was halfway home.

01:17:54.120 --> 01:17:56.200
You should have driven faster.

01:17:57.400 --> 01:17:58.959
Ah, yes. Yes!

01:17:58.960 --> 01:18:00.719
Very good.

01:18:00.720 --> 01:18:03.319
Now you see... Perfect.

01:18:03.320 --> 01:18:05.719
What is? Are you going to tell us?

01:18:05.720 --> 01:18:07.280
Try looking yourself.

01:18:08.960 --> 01:18:12.239
Look for what?
Is the murderer in these photographs?

01:18:12.240 --> 01:18:14.039
It's not what's
in the photographs,

01:18:14.040 --> 01:18:16.119
it's what's not in them.
Not in any of them.

01:18:16.120 --> 01:18:17.399
Sherlock?

01:18:17.400 --> 01:18:19.760
The showing-off thing,
we've discussed it before...

01:18:21.440 --> 01:18:24.999
There is always a man at a wedding
who is not in any photograph,

01:18:25.000 --> 01:18:26.799
who can go anywhere.

01:18:26.800 --> 01:18:29.599
And even carry an equipment bag
around with him if he likes.

01:18:29.600 --> 01:18:31.559
And you never even see his face.

01:18:31.560 --> 01:18:33.160
You only ever see...

01:18:41.960 --> 01:18:43.239
The camera.

01:18:43.240 --> 01:18:44.759
What are you doing? What is this?

01:18:44.760 --> 01:18:47.399
Jonathan Small, today's
substitute wedding photographer,

01:18:47.400 --> 01:18:49.279
known to us as the Mayfly Man.

01:18:49.280 --> 01:18:53.999
His brother was one of the raw
recruits killed in that incursion.

01:18:54.000 --> 01:18:56.079
Johnny sought revenge on Sholto,

01:18:56.080 --> 01:18:58.399
worked his way through
Sholto's staff,

01:18:58.400 --> 01:18:59.599
found what he needed.

01:18:59.600 --> 01:19:01.799
An invitation to a wedding.

01:19:01.800 --> 01:19:05.319
The one time Sholto would
have to be out in public.

01:19:05.320 --> 01:19:09.119
So he made his plan
and rehearsed the murder,

01:19:09.120 --> 01:19:12.640
